  "@type": "SoftwareSourceCode",
  "identifier": "regsensitivity",
  "description": "Sensitivity analysis for linear regression coefficients in the presence of omitted variables. Implements the identified-set and breakdown-point analyses of 'Diegert', 'Masten' and 'Poirier' (2026) <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2206.02303>, 'Oster' (2019) <doi:10.1080/07350015.2016.1227711> and 'Masten' and 'Poirier' (2026) <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2208.00552>. Provides bounds on regression coefficients under relaxations of the no-omitted-variables assumption indexed by interpretable sensitivity parameters, the breakdown point of a hypothesis about the long-regression coefficient, and plotting helpers.",
  "name": "regsensitivity: Regression Sensitivity Analysis for Omitted Variable Bias",
